\par EQUIPMENT\line \line }{\rtlch\fcs1 \ab\af1\afs32 \ltrch\fcs0 \b\f1\fs32\cf19\highlight9\insrsid12197632\charrsid12197632 1. Introduction}{\rtlch\fcs1 \ab\af1\afs44 \ltrch\fcs0 \b\f1\fs44\cf18\insrsid12197632 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \ab\af1\afs32 \ltrch\fcs0 \b\f1\fs32\cf8\insrsid12197632 1. Introduction
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af1 \ltrch\fcs0 \f1\cf1\insrsid12197632 In order to ensure safe systems of work and to prevent transmission of
\par infection, it is essential that decontamination of equipment after use on a
\par patient is undertaken to prevent the transmission of infection. This is in
\par accordance with the requirements of the }{\rtlch\fcs1 \ai\af1 \ltrch\fcs0 \i\f1\cf1\insrsid12197632 Health and Social Care Act 2008:
\par Code of Practice on the prevention and control of infections and related
\par guidanc}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af1 \ltrch\fcs0 \f1\cf1\insrsid12197632 e.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \ab\af1\afs32 \ltrch\fcs0 \b\f1\fs32\cf19\insrsid12197632\charrsid12197632 2. Defin\line }{\rtlch\fcs1 \ab\af1\afs32 \ltrch\fcs0 \b\f1\fs32\cf19\highlight9\insrsid12197632\charrsid12197632 2. Definitions}{\rtlch\fcs1 \ab\af1\afs32 
\ltrch\fcs0 \b\f1\fs32\cf8\insrsid12197632 \line ns
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af40 \ltrch\fcs0 \f40\cf1\insrsid12197632 \bullet  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \ab\af1 \ltrch\fcs0 \b\f1\cf18\insrsid12197632 Contamination: }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af1 \ltrch\fcs0 \f1\cf1\insrsid12197632 The soiling of an object with harmful, potentially
\par infectious or unwanted matter.\line 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af40 \ltrch\fcs0 \f40\cf1\insrsid12197632 \bullet  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \ab\af1 \ltrch\fcs0 \b\f1\cf18\insrsid12197632 Decontamination: }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af1 \ltrch\fcs0 \f1\cf1\insrsid12197632 A combination of processes that removes or
\par destroys contamination.\line 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af40 \ltrch\fcs0 \f40\cf1\insrsid12197632 \bullet  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \ab\af1 \ltrch\fcs0 \b\f1\cf18\insrsid12197632 Cleaning: }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af1 \ltrch\fcs0 \f1\cf1\insrsid12197632 A process that will physically remove contamination
\par (blood, vomit, faeces, etc.) and many microorganisms
\par using detergent and water.\line 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af40 \ltrch\fcs0 \f40\cf1\insrsid12197632 \bullet  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \ab\af1 \ltrch\fcs0 \b\f1\cf18\insrsid12197632 Disinfection: }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af1 \ltrch\fcs0 \f1\cf1\insrsid12197632 A process to reduce the number of micro-organisms
\par to a less harmful level. The ability to kill spores is
\par dependent on the type of disinfectant used.\line 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af40 \ltrch\fcs0 \f40\cf1\insrsid12197632 \bullet  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \ab\af1 \ltrch\fcs0 \b\f1\cf18\insrsid12197632 Sterilisation: }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af1 \ltrch\fcs0 \f1\cf1\insrsid12197632 A process that removes or destroys all organisms
\par including spores.\line \line }{\rtlch\fcs1 \ab\af1\afs32 \ltrch\fcs0 \b\f1\fs32\cf19\highlight9\insrsid12197632\charrsid12197632 3. Evidence of decontamination}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af1 \ltrch\fcs0 \f1\cf19\insrsid12197632\charrsid12197632 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \ab\af1\afs32 \ltrch\fcs0 \b\f1\fs32\cf8\insrsid12197632 3. Evidence of decontamination
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af1 \ltrch\fcs0 \f1\cf1\insrsid12197632 It is recommended that monthly audits to assess the standard of cleanliness of
\par equipment be carried out. An audit tool is available to download at\line 
\par }{\field{\*\fldinst {\rtlch\fcs1 \af1 \ltrch\fcs0 \f1\cf2\insrsid12197632  HYPERLINK "http://www.infectionpreventioncontrol.co.uk" }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af1 \ltrch\fcs0 \f1\cf2\insrsid5012688 {\*\datafield 
00d0c9ea79f9bace118c8200aa004ba90b0200000003000000e0c9ea79f9bace118c8200aa004ba90b7200000068007400740070003a002f002f007700770077002e0069006e00660065006300740069006f006e00700072006500760065006e00740069006f006e0063006f006e00740072006f006c002e0063006f002e00
75006b002f000000795881f43b1d7f48af2c825dc485276300000000a5ab000032006000}}}{\fldrslt {\rtlch\fcs1 \af1 \ltrch\fcs0 \cs17\f1\ul\cf17\insrsid12197632\charrsid14683248 www.infectionpreventioncontrol.co.uk}}}\sectd \ltrsect
\linex0\headery708\footery708\colsx708\endnhere\sectlinegrid360\sectdefaultcl\sftnbj {\rtlch\fcs1 \af1 \ltrch\fcs0 \f1\cf2\insrsid12197632 \line }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af1 \ltrch\fcs0 \f1\cf1\insrsid12197632 .
\par Re-usable medical equipment that has been cleaned or disinfected should be
\par labelled, e.g. with \lquote I am clean\rquote  indicator tape or label/documentation giving
\par details of the date of cleaning and signed by the person who performed the
\par decontamination.\line 
\par It is also recommended that equipment not in regular use should be checked
\par on a monthly basis and decontaminated as appropriate and re-labelled.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \ab\af1\afs20 \ltrch\fcs0 \b\f1\fs20\cf8\insrsid12197632\charrsid12197632 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \ab\af1\afs32 \ltrch\fcs0 \b\f1\fs32\cf19\highlight9\insrsid5012688 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \ab\af1\afs32 \ltrch\fcs0 \b\f1\fs32\cf19\highlight9\insrsid12197632\charrsid12197632 4. Methods of decontamination}{\rtlch\fcs1 \ab\af1\afs32 \ltrch\fcs0 \b\f1\fs32\cf19\insrsid12197632 \line }{\rtlch\fcs1 \ab\af1\afs32 \ltrch\fcs0 
\b\f1\fs32\cf19\insrsid12197632\charrsid12197632  of}{\rtlch\fcs1 \ab\af1\afs32 \ltrch\fcs0 \b\f1\fs32\cf8\insrsid12197632  decontamination}{\rtlch\fcs1 \ab\af1\afs72 \ltrch\fcs0 \b\f1\fs72\cf8\insrsid12197632\charrsid12197632 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af1 \ltrch\fcs0 \f1\cf1\insrsid12197632 There are 3 levels of decontamination, cleaning, disinfection and sterilisation.\line 
\par All equipment should be adequately decontaminated after use on a patient.
\par The method recommended will depend on the manufacturer\rquote s instructions, a
\par risk assessment of the procedure and the item being used in accordance with
\par Control of Substances Hazardous to Health (COSHH) Regulations (see Section
\par 12 Infection risks and categories).
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \ab\af1\afs32 \ltrch\fcs0 \b\f1\fs32\cf8\insrsid12197632 5
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \ab\af1\afs32 \ltrch\fcs0 \b\f1\fs32\cf19\highlight9\insrsid12197632\charrsid12197632 5. Cleaning}{\rtlch\fcs1 \ab\af1\afs32 \ltrch\fcs0 \b\f1\fs32\cf8\insrsid12197632  Cle\line aning
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af40 \ltrch\fcs0 \f40\cf1\insrsid12197632 \bullet  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af1 \ltrch\fcs0 \f1\cf1\insrsid12197632 Detergent wipes or detergent and warm water and single use cloths are
\par recommended.\line 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af40 \ltrch\fcs0 \f40\cf1\insrsid12197632 \bullet  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af1 \ltrch\fcs0 \f1\cf1\insrsid12197632 Cleaning is }{\rtlch\fcs1 \ab\af1 \ltrch\fcs0 \b\f1\cf1\insrsid12197632 essential }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af1 \ltrch\fcs0 
\f1\cf1\insrsid12197632 before disinfection or sterilisation is carried out.\line 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af40 \ltrch\fcs0 \f40\cf1\insrsid12197632 \bullet  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af1 \ltrch\fcs0 \f1\cf1\insrsid12197632 All equipment that has been cleaned must be dried thoroughly before
\par storage.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \ab\af1\afs32 \ltrch\fcs0 \b\f1\fs32\cf8\insrsid12197632 6
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \ab\af1\afs32 \ltrch\fcs0 \b\f1\fs32\cf19\highlight9\insrsid12197632\charrsid12197632 6. Disinfection}{\rtlch\fcs1 \ab\af1\afs32 \ltrch\fcs0 \b\f1\fs32\insrsid12197632\charrsid12197632  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \ab\af1\afs32 \ltrch\fcs0 
\b\f1\fs32\insrsid12197632 \line \line }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af40 \ltrch\fcs0 \f40\cf1\insrsid12197632 \bullet  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af1 \ltrch\fcs0 \f1\cf1\insrsid12197632 Disinfectants can be in the form of a wipe, e.g. Clinell Universal, Steri-7
\par extra or as chlorine releasing tablets, liquids or granules, such as Haztabs,
\par Presept, Chlor-Clean, Tristel Fuse.\line 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af40 \ltrch\fcs0 \f40\cf1\insrsid12197632 \bullet  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af1 \ltrch\fcs0 \f1\cf1\insrsid12197632 A disinfectant will not be effective if there is dirt or visible soiling present,
\par e.g. urine, blood. Therefore, if the disinfectant does not contain a detergent
\par the equipment should be cleaned before a disinfectant is used.\line 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af40 \ltrch\fcs0 \f40\cf1\insrsid12197632 \bullet  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af1 \ltrch\fcs0 \f1\cf1\insrsid12197632 Some disinfectant products contain both a detergent and a disinfectant, e.g.
\par Clinell Universal wipes, Chlor-Clean releasing tablets. This means
\par equipment does not need to be cleaned before disinfection.\line 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af40 \ltrch\fcs0 \f40\cf1\insrsid12197632 \bullet  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af1 \ltrch\fcs0 \f1\cf1\insrsid12197632 When disinfecting equipment always follow the manufacturer\rquote s instructions,
\par some equipment will have specific instructions which should be followed,
\par e.g. Propulse machine, peak flow.\line 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af40 \ltrch\fcs0 \f40\cf1\insrsid12197632 \bullet  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af1 \ltrch\fcs0 \f1\cf1\insrsid12197632 A disinfectant should be used for any equipment contaminated with
\par splashes of blood. The appropriate disinfectant should have virucidal
\par properties effective against hepatitis B, hepatitis C and HIV.\line 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af40 \ltrch\fcs0 \f40\cf1\insrsid12197632 \bullet  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af1 \ltrch\fcs0 \f1\cf1\insrsid12197632 A disinfectant should be used for equipment that has been in contact with a
\par patient with a known or suspected infection, non-intact skin, mucous
\par membranes or body fluids.\line 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af40 \ltrch\fcs0 \f40\cf1\insrsid12197632 \bullet  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af1 \ltrch\fcs0 \f1\cf1\insrsid12197632 To ensure a disinfectant solution works effectively, it is important that the
\par correct amount of disinfectant and water are used. If a weaker solution is
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \ab\af1\afs20 \ltrch\fcs0 \b\f1\fs20\cf8\insrsid12197632\charrsid12197632 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af1 \ltrch\fcs0 \f1\cf1\insrsid12197632 
\par used, the micro-organisms will not be killed, too strong, and equipment or
\par surfaces can be damaged.\line 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af40 \ltrch\fcs0 \f40\cf1\insrsid12197632 \bullet  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af1 \ltrch\fcs0 \f1\cf1\insrsid12197632 If a chlorine-based solution is used it should be at a dilution of 1,000 ppm.\line 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af40 \ltrch\fcs0 \f40\cf1\insrsid12197632 \bullet  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af1 \ltrch\fcs0 \f1\cf1\insrsid12197632 As diluted chlorine-based disinfectant solutions are unstable and become
\par less effective after 24 hours, a new solution should be made each day.\line 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af40 \ltrch\fcs0 \f40\cf1\insrsid12197632 \bullet  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af1 \ltrch\fcs0 \f1\cf1\insrsid12197632 When using disinfectant products, always wear disposable gloves and an
\par apron and if indicated, eye protection.\line 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af40 \ltrch\fcs0 \f40\cf1\insrsid12197632 \bullet  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af1 \ltrch\fcs0 \f1\cf1\insrsid12197632 COSHH regulations must be adhered to at all times.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \ab\af1\afs32 \ltrch\fcs0 \b\f1\fs32\cf8\insrsid12197632 7. Sterilisation
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \ab\af1\afs32 \ltrch\fcs0 \b\f1\fs32\cf19\highlight9\insrsid12197632\charrsid12197632 7. Sterilisation}{\rtlch\fcs1 \ab\af1\afs32 \ltrch\fcs0 \b\f1\fs32\insrsid12197632 \line }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af1 \ltrch\fcs0 \f1\cf1\insrsid12197632 \line 
The use of bench top steam sterilisers (autoclaves) is not recommended.
\par Sterilisation is a specialist means of decontamination of equipment. Reusable
\par items requiring sterilisation after use must be sent to an accredited
\par Decontamination Services Facility. Alternatively, single use disposable
\par equipment should be used.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \ab\af1\afs32 \ltrch\fcs0 \b\f1\fs32\cf8\insrsid12197632 8. Decontamination of equipment prior to
\par 8. Decontamination of equipment prior to
